Meleket API Dashboard

API documentation for accessing project data

Project Endpoints

GET/api/projects

Returns all projects data

Example response:

[
  {
    "id": 1,
    "title": "Project Title",
    "slug": "project-slug",
    "excerpt": "Brief project description",
    "coverImage": "/path/to/image.jpg",
    "featured": true
  }
]
GET/api/projects?featured=true

Returns only featured projects

GET/api/projects?slug=project-slug

Returns detailed data for a specific project

Example response:

{
  "id": 1,
  "title": "Project Title",
  "slug": "project-slug",
  "excerpt": "Brief project description",
  "coverImage": "/path/to/image.jpg",
  "content": "Detailed project content...",
  "client": "Client Name",
  "timeline": "3 months",
  "teamSize": 5,
  "platforms": [
    "Web",
    "Mobile"
  ],
  "technologies": [
    "React",
    "Next.js"
  ],
  "challenges": [
    "Challenge 1",
    "Challenge 2"
  ],
  "solutions": [
    "Solution 1",
    "Solution 2"
  ],
  "results": [
    "Result 1",
    "Result 2"
  ],
  "testimonials": [
    {
      "quote": "Great work!",
      "author": "John Doe",
      "role": "CEO"
    }
  ]
}

Using the API

You can access these endpoints using any HTTP client. Example using fetch:

// Get all projects
fetch('/api/projects')
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => console.log(data));

// Get a specific project
fetch('/api/projects?slug=habesha-market-campaign')
  .then(response => response.json())
  .then(data => console.log(data));
